<p><b>Summary executions;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Torture;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged beating and subsequent death in custody. According to the information 
received, on 3 June 2011, Mr. Hassan Mahammad El Hmidi was arrested by a group 
of the anti-drug police along with his father and two brothers.  All three individuals 
were taken to the former premises of the preventive security apparatus located in 
Salah El Din Street in Central Gaza Strip. Mr. Hassan Mahammad El Hmidi&#8223;s 
</p>
<p>brother and father were reportedly released, while Mr. Hassan Mahammad El Hmidi 
remained detained. He had reportedly been subjected to intermittent beating which 
lasted for hours. On 10 June, Mr. Hassan Mahammad El Hmidi had died in Al-Shifa 
hospital after having undergone head surgery. 
</p>
<p> 
 
 
 
 
