<p>Allegations of continuous excessive use of force by law enforcement authorities 
against, and the arrest and detention of protesters belonging to the Maldivian 
Democratic Party (MDP). According to the information received, on 29 February 
2012 the Maldives Security Forces reportedly assaulted women protesters who 
peacefully marked their opposition to the current Government. On 7 and 19 March 
2012 Maldives Security Forces reportedly attacked MDP protesters in Mal&#233;, in the 
context of demonstrations held to express dissent and opposition to the current 
Government. According to reports, since 7 February 2012, 376 persons have been 
detained. Many allegedly do not have access to family nor lawyers. Reportedly, the 
Government did not release the names and number of the detainees.   
